From: Hao Luo <haoluo@google.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Dec 2021 16:31:45 -0800
Subject: bpf: Replace ARG_XXX_OR_NULL with ARG_XXX | PTR_MAYBE_NULL
Patch-mainline: v5.17-rc1
Git-commit: 48946bd6a5d695c50b34546864b79c1f910a33c1
References: bsc#1194111 bsc#1194765 bsc#1196261 CVE-2021-4204 CVE-2022-0500 CVE-2022-23222

We have introduced a new type to make bpf_arg composable, by
reserving high bits of bpf_arg to represent flags of a type.

One of the flags is PTR_MAYBE_NULL which indicates a pointer
may be NULL. When applying this flag to an arg_type, it means
the arg can take NULL pointer. This patch switches the
qualified arg_types to use this flag. The arg_types changed
in this patch include:

1. ARG_PTR_TO_MAP_VALUE_OR_NULL
2. ARG_PTR_TO_MEM_OR_NULL
3. ARG_PTR_TO_CTX_OR_NULL
4. ARG_PTR_TO_SOCKET_OR_NULL
5. ARG_PTR_TO_ALLOC_MEM_OR_NULL
6. ARG_PTR_TO_STACK_OR_NULL

This patch does not eliminate the use of these arg_types, instead
it makes them an alias to the 'ARG_XXX | PTR_MAYBE_NULL'.

